= Changing Concepts About Early Angiosperms
- Early theories (e.g., "Hamamelidae" as relictual) have been revised based on wood anatomy and DNA studies.
- Wind-pollinated trees with simple flowers are now considered derived, not primitive.
- The "ranalean flower" hypothesis (Magnolia-type as relictual) is still relevant but refined.
- Earliest angiosperm fossils (pollen) date to >130 million years ago (Lower Cretaceous).
- Earliest leaf fossils: _Magnoliaephyllum_, _Ficophyllum_.
- Angiosperms likely originated in the Jurassic Period.

