= Monocots
- Monophyletic group, likely arose 80-100 mya.
- Key features:
  - Single cotyledon.
  - Parallel leaf venation.
  - Scattered vascular bundles (atactostele).
  - No ordinary secondary growth (wood).
  - Flower parts in multiples of 3.
  - Uniaperturate pollen.

