== Commelinoid Monocots
- Clade defined by UV-fluorescent cell wall compounds and starch in pollen/endosperm.
- Includes: Arecales, Poales, Zingiberales, Commelinales.

=== Arecales (Palms)
- Family Arecaceae.
- Woody-like trunks (primary thickening meristem).
- Large compound leaves (fronds).

#figure(
  image(images.at("23-19").path, width: 50%),
  caption: [#images.at("23-19").caption]
