=== Lamiids (Euasterids I)
- **Solanaceae** (Nightshades): Potato, tomato, tobacco; often poisonous alkaloids.
- **Lamiaceae** (Mints): Square stems, aromatic oils, bilabiate flowers.
- **Rubiaceae**: Coffee.

=== Campanulids (Euasterids II)
- **Asteraceae** (Composites): Largest eudicot family (Sunflowers, Daisies).
  - Head inflorescence (capitulum) with ray and disk florets.
  - Fruit is an achene (cypsela).
  - Chemical defenses: Sesquiterpene lactones.
- **Apiaceae** (Umbellifers): Carrots, parsley; umbel inflorescence.

